org.apache.orc

Interface DataReader

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Cloneable

    public interface DataReader
extends AutoCloseable, Cloneable
    An abstract data reader that IO formats can use to read bytes from underlying storage.

      • readFileData

        DiskRangeList readFileData(DiskRangeList range,
                           long baseOffset,
                           boolean doForceDirect)
                    throws IOException
        Reads the data. Note that for the cases such as zero-copy read, caller must release the disk ranges produced after being done with them. Call isTrackingDiskRanges to find out if this is needed.
        Parameters:
        range - List if disk ranges to read. Ranges with data will be ignored.
        baseOffset - Base offset from the start of the file of the ranges in disk range list.
        doForceDirect - Whether the data should be read into direct buffers.
        Returns:
        New or modified list of DiskRange-s, where all the ranges are filled with data.
        Throws:
        IOException

      • isTrackingDiskRanges

        boolean isTrackingDiskRanges()
        Whether the user should release buffers created by readFileData. See readFileData javadoc.

      • releaseBuffer

        void releaseBuffer(ByteBuffer toRelease)
        Releases buffers created by readFileData. See readFileData javadoc.
        Parameters:
        toRelease - The buffer to release.

      • clone

        DataReader clone()
        Clone the entire state of the DataReader with the assumption that the clone will be closed at a different time. Thus, any file handles in the implementation need to be cloned.
        Returns:
        a new instance
